With a list comprehension on `d.items`, we can apply `val.format(**d)` on each value to interpolate the values with the dict itself:

&gt;     &gt;&gt;&gt; d = {&#39;A&#39;:&#39;x&#39;, &#39;B&#39;:&#39;y&#39;, &#39;C&#39;:&#39;{A}_foo&#39;, &#39;D&#39;:&#39;bar_{B}&#39;}
&gt;     &gt;&gt;&gt; o = dict([ (key, val.format(**d)) for key,val in d.items() ])
